<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 30 at 10:12PM CDT until April 30 at 11:00PM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1045 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN BRADLEY AND SOUTHWESTERN DREW COUNTIES...
At 1012 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 8 miles west of Old
Milo, or 9 miles north of West Crossett, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Ingalls...                        Prairie Grove...
Mt Olive in Bradley County...     Johnsonville...
Vick...                           Lacey...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
